{"id":859,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":221,"title":"Cam7 - Test 4 - Part 1","subtitle":"Homestay Application Conversation","level":"B1","parts":65,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam7-test-4-part-1.859/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/0-ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1.mp3","transcript":"Yes, what can I do for you?\nMy friend is in homestay...\nand she really enjoys it...\nso I'd like to join a family as well.\nOkay, so let me get some details.\nWhat's your name?\nMy name is Keiko Yuichini.\nCould you spell your family name for me?\nIt's... Yuichini,\nthat's YUICHINI.\nAnd your first name?\nIt's Keiko.\nKEIKO.\nThat's Keiko Yuichini... okay...\nand you're female.\nAnd your nationality?\nI'm Japanese.\nRight and could I see your passport, please?\nHere it is...\nOkay... your passport number is JO 6337...\nAnd you're how old?\nI'm 28 years old.\nNow, you live at one of the colleges... which one?\nWillow College, umm...\nRoom 21C.\nRight, 21C Willow College,\nand how long are you planning on staying with homestay?\nAbout four months...\nlonger if I like it...\nAnd what course are you enrolled in?\nWell, I've enrolled for twenty weeks in the...\num... Advanced English Studies\nbecause I need help with my writing,\nand I'm nearly at the end of my first five-week course.\nOkay... Do you have any preference for a family with children or without children?\nI prefer... I mean, I like young children,\nbut I'd like to be with older people...\nyou know... adults... someone around my age.\nOkay.\nAnd what about pets?\nI am a veterinarian so that's fine... the more the better.\nAll right, now what about you?\nAre you a vegetarian or do you have any special food requirements?\nNo, I am not a vegetarian...\nbut I don't eat a lot of meat...\nI really like seafood.\nAnd what are your hobbies?\nI like reading and going to the movies.\nDo you play any sports?\nYes, I joined the handball team,\nbut I didn't like that... so I stopped playing.\nNow I play tennis on the weekend with my friends...\nAlright,\nlet's see, name, age, now the location.\nAre you familiar with the public transport system?\nNo, I'm not really because I have been living on campus,\nI've been to the city a few times on the bus, but they are always late.\nWhat about the trains?\nI like catching the train, they are much faster.\nNow, let me go check on the computer and see who I've got...\nListen, leave it with me... I'll check my records and I'll give you details this afternoon.\nThank you for helping me!\nIt's a pleasure.\nBye.\nBye.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:20","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Yes, what can I do for you?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/1.mp3","time_start":0.3,"time_end":1.97},{"position":2,"content":"My friend is in homestay...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/2.mp3","time_start":2.22,"time_end":4.58},{"position":3,"content":"and she really enjoys it...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/3.mp3","time_start":4.58,"time_end":6.78},{"position":4,"content":"so I'd like to join a family as well.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/4.mp3","time_start":6.78,"time_end":9.58},{"position":5,"content":"Okay, so let me get some details.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/5.mp3","time_start":9.58,"time_end":12.57},{"position":6,"content":"What's your name?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/6.mp3","time_start":12.9,"time_end":14.1},{"position":7,"content":"My name is Keiko Yuichini.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/7.mp3","time_start":14.38,"time_end":16.93},{"position":8,"content":"Could you spell your family name for me?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/8.mp3","time_start":17.17,"time_end":19.5},{"position":9,"content":"It's... Yuichini,","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/9.mp3","time_start":19.7,"time_end":21.54},{"position":10,"content":"that's YUICHINI.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/10.mp3","time_start":21.54,"time_end":28.89},{"position":11,"content":"And your first name?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/11.mp3","time_start":28.89,"time_end":30.32},{"position":12,"content":"It's Keiko.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/12.mp3","time_start":30.32,"time_end":31.98},{"position":13,"content":"KEIKO.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/13.mp3","time_start":32.32,"time_end":36.45},{"position":14,"content":"That's Keiko Yuichini... okay...","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/14.mp3","time_start":36.45,"time_end":39.63},{"position":15,"content":"and you're female.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-7-test-4-part-1-2023-07-31-19-31-20/15.mp3","time_start":39.63,"time_end":41.33},{"position":16,"content":"And your nationality?","audio_url":"https://daily